Saman Fleming went missing from her home in Anderson, Indiana, on April 5 . 
  Her body was found Friday wrapped in plastic and doused in bleach . 
  Police believe a woman pretending to be a social worker lured her to Gary by posing as a CPS worker and convinced her to come with her to steal her baby . 
  Fleming gave birth to her daughter Serenity three weeks ago . 
  The baby was found safe at the home of the suspect in Gary . 
  The suspect lives in Gary and is in police custody . 
 